oha]], hosts 103 embassies. Several other countries are accredited to Qatar from other capitals.\n\n== Embassies ==\n;Doha\n\n{| \n|\n*{{AFG}}\n*{{ALB}}\n*{{ALG}}\n*{{ARG}}\n*{{ARM}}\n*{{AUS}}\n*{{AUT}}\n*{{AZE}}\n*{{BAN}}\n*{{BLR}}\n*{{BEL}}\n*{{BEN}}\n*{{BIH}}\n*{{BRA}}\n*{{BRU}}\n*{{BUL}}\n*{{BUR}}\n*{{CAN}}\n*{{Flag|Central African Republic}}\n*{{CHA}}\n*{{CHN}}\n*{{CRI}}\n*{{Flag|Croatia}}\n*{{CUB}} \n*{{CYP}} \n*{{DJI}}\n*{{DOM}}\n*{{ECU}}\n*{{ESA}}\n*{{ERI}}\n*{{Flag|Eswatini}}\n*{{Flag|Ethiopia}}\n*{{FRA}} \n*{{GAM}}\n|valign=top|\n*{{GEO}}\n*{{GER}}\n*{{GHA}}\n*{{GRE}}\n*{{HAI}}\n*{{HUN}}\n*{{IND}}\n*{{INA}} \n*{{IRI}}\n*{{IRQ}}\n*{{ITA}} \n*{{Flag|Ivory Coast}}\n*{{JPN}}\n*{{JOR}}\n*{{KAZ}}\n*{{KEN}}\n*{{KUW}}\n*{{Flag|Kyrgyzstan}}\n*{{LIB}}\n*{{Flag|Liberia}}\n*{{LBA}}\n*{{MAS}} \n*{{Flag|Mali}}\n*{{MTN}}\n*{{MEX}}\n*{{Flag|Moldova}}\n*{{MAR}}\n*{{NEP}}\n*{{NED}}\n*{{NIG}}\n*{{NGR}} \n*{{MKD}}\n*{{OMA}}\n*{{PAK}}\n|valign=top|\n*{{Flag|Palestine}}\n*{{PAN}}\n*{{PAR}}\n*{{PER}}\n*{{PHI}}\n*{{POL}}\n*{{POR}}\n*{{ROU}}\n*{{RUS}} \n*{{SEN}}\n*{{SRB}}\n*{{SIN}}\n*{{SOM}}\n*{{RSA}}\n*{{ROK}} \n*{{ESP}} \n*{{SRI}}\n*{{SUD}}\n*{{SWE}}\n*{{SUI}}\n*{{Flag|Tajikistan}}\n*{{TAN}}\n*{{THA}}\n*{{TUN}}\n*{{TUR}}\n*{{UGA}}\n*{{UKR}}\n*{{GBR}} \n*{{USA}} \n*{{URU}}\n*{{VEN}}\n*{{VIE}}\n|}\n\n=== Representative Offices ===\n*{{Flag|Northern Cyprus}} (Representative Office)\n*{{Flag|Egypt}} (Egypt Interests Section, Embassy of Greece)[http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/270336/Egypt/Politics-/Greek-embassy-takes-on-diplomatic-representation-o.aspx]\n*{{Flag|Yemen}} (Yemen Interests Section, Embassy of Sudan)\n\n==Embassies to open==\n*{{KOS}}\n**[[Doha]] (Embassy to open)\n\n== Former embassies ==\n* {{BHR}} \n* {{COM}}\n* {{EGY}} \n* {{KSA}} \n* {{UAE}} \n* {{YEM}}\n\n== Accredited embassies ==\nResident in [[Riyadh]] unless otherwise noted\n{| \n|\n*{{Flag|Angola}} (Abu Dhabi)\n*{{Flag|Botswana}} (Kuwait City)\n*{{Flag|Cambodia}} (Kuwait City)\n*{{CMR}}\n*{{CHI}}